Lab 2 --> write requirements for the project ALMADESTINO
-> write major functionalities
 + full sentence, keep 'system' as the subject of the sentence
 + Identify functional requirements, write i/p, o/p and description
 -> work on sub requirements
 eg. R1
   -- R11
   -- R12
   -- R13 etc
-----------------------------============------------------------------  
			      ALMADESTINO
-> Major functionalities :
 > System allows you to search packages ; Fiter them as per your need.
 > System allows you to book a package as per your select date and time to select place.
 > Our System even provides the facility to cancel booking with 80% cashback.
 > Go Cashless ! Pay online.
 
-> Functional Requirements
 > R1: System provides facility to a vendor to add a package.
     R2_1 :
      => Description : System checks if user is logged in or not
      => I/P : Username & Password
      => O/P :	Yes/No
     R1_2 :
      => Description : System checks if logged in user is a vendor or not
      => I/P : Username & Password
      => O/P : Yes/No
     R1_3 :
     => Description : System checks for the travelling date
     =>	I/P :  Date/TimeStamp 
     =>	O/P : Valid or Invalid.
     R1_4 :	
     => Description : System checks for the starting place 
     => I/P :City, state & Country limited to Asia
     => O/P : Valid or Invalid
     R1_5 :
     => Description : System checks for the reaching place
     => I/P :City, state & Country limited to Asia
     => O/P : Valid or Invalid
     R1_6 :
     => Description : System checks for cost
     => I/P : Integer
     => O/P : Valid or Invalid
 > R2 : System allows you to book a package 
      R2_1 :
      => Description : System checks if user is logged in or not
      => I/P : Username & Password
      => O/P :	Yes/No
      R2_2 :
      => Description : System checks if the package exists
      => I/P : Package info.
      => O/P : Yes/No      
      R2_2 :
     => Description : If package exists, check its availablity
     => I/P : Package info.
     => O/P : Yes/No 	
 > R3 :  System allows you to cancel a package
      R3_1 :
      => Description : System checks if user is logged in or not
      => I/P : Username & Password
      => O/P :	Yes/No
     R3_2 :
     => Description : System checks if user has booked that package or not
     => I/P : Package Info.
     => O/P : Yes/No
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      
      
     
